# Assuming Y is actual values and Y_hat_model1 to Y_hat_model5 are predicted values
# Step 1: Compute Errors
error1 <- Y - Y_hat_model1
error2 <- Y - Y_hat_model2
error3 <- Y - Y_hat_model3
error4 <- Y - Y_hat_model4
error5 <- Y - Y_hat_model5
normalize_z <- function(x) {
  (x - mean(x)) / sd(x)
}
norm_error1 <- normalize_z(error1)
norm_error2 <- normalize_z(error2)
norm_error3 <- normalize_z(error3)
norm_error4 <- normalize_z(error4)
norm_error5 <- normalize_z(error5)
# Step 2: Compute RMSE for each model
rmse <- function(e) sqrt(mean(e^2))

rmse1 <- rmse(error1)
rmse2 <- rmse(error2)
rmse3 <- rmse(error3)
rmse4 <- rmse(error4)
rmse5 <- rmse(error5)

# Combine RMSEs
rmse_values <- c(rmse1, rmse2, rmse3, rmse4, rmse5)
names(rmse_values) <- paste0("Model", 1:5)

# Step 3: Normalize RMSE (min-max normalization)
normalized_rmse <- (rmse_values - min(rmse_values)) / (max(rmse_values) - min(rmse_values))

# Step 4: Find the best model (with minimum RMSE)
best_model <- names(rmse_values)[which.min(rmse_values)]

# Output
print("RMSE for each model:")
## [1] "RMSE for each model:"
print(rmse_values)
##       Model1       Model2       Model3       Model4       Model5 
##     8.288084     7.934377 20961.883820 81339.410152     6.181692
print("Normalized RMSE:")
## [1] "Normalized RMSE:"
print(normalized_rmse)
##       Model1       Model2       Model3       Model4       Model5 
## 2.589829e-05 2.154943e-05 2.576524e-01 1.000000e+00 0.000000e+00
cat("Best fitted model is:", best_model, "\n")
## Best fitted model is: Model5

  new_RSS
  if (new_RSS > Epsilon){

  }

# Given values
thetabias <- 251.671653135     # selected parameter 0
thetaone <- 0.227168908        # selected parameter 1
thetatwo <- -0.036521863       # constant 2
thetathree <- -0.003650664     # constant 3
Epsilon <- RSS_Model_5 * 2     # acceptance threshold
num <- 200                     # number of iterations
# Initialize vectors for rejected samples
rejected_theta0 <- c()
rejected_theta1 <- c()
# Loop to simulate samples and calculate RSS
for (i in 1:num) {
  # Sample theta0 and theta1 from uniform distributions
  range1 <- runif(1, -thetabias, thetabias)
  range2 <- runif(1, -thetaone, thetaone)

  # Combine all parameters into one vector
  New_thetahat <- matrix(c(range1, range2, thetatwo, thetathree), ncol = 1)
  
  # Compute predicted Y
  New_Y_Hat <- X_model5 %*% New_thetahat
  
  # Calculate new RSS
  new_RSS <- sum((Y - New_Y_Hat)^2)
  
  # Store rejected samples where RSS > epsilon
  if (new_RSS > Epsilon) {
    rejected_theta0 <- c(rejected_theta0, range1)
    rejected_theta1 <- c(rejected_theta1, range2)
  }
}

# Combine into a data frame
rejection_area <- data.frame(
  Theta0 = rejected_theta0,
  Theta1 = rejected_theta1,
  Theta2 = rep(thetatwo, length(rejected_theta0)),
  Theta3 = rep(thetathree, length(rejected_theta0))
)
# View summary
summary(rejection_area)
